org.symphonyoss.client.services

Class RoomService

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.symphonyoss.client.services.RoomService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RoomServiceEventListener, RoomServiceListener

    public class RoomService
extends java.lang.Object
implements RoomServiceListener, RoomServiceEventListener
    The room service provides capabilities that support room access and events. The running service will construct room objects detected from new message events. The service supports listeners that provide callbacks to all registered room events and general messaging.

    Its important to note the distinction between creating a room and joining a room. Creating a room implies the creation of the room object, but not the monitoring of it by the service. You must explicitly join a room (register with the RoomService) in order to receive individual room events.

    • Method Detail

      • createRoom

        public Room createRoom(SymRoomAttributes symRoomAttributes)
                throws RoomException
        Create a new room object from SymRoomAttributes provided. The room object will be enriched with all associated room metadata at the point of creation.

        Note: Future lifecycle room events are not automatically reflected in the created room object. updated.

        Parameters:
        symRoomAttributes - Room attributes required to create the room object
        Returns:
        Fully populated Room object
        Throws:
        RoomException - Exception generated from the logical creation of the room object

      • getRoom

        public Room getRoom(java.lang.String stream)
        Return registered room by provided stream. The room object must be registered to the service through the joinRoom(Room) method.
        Parameters:
        stream - Stream ID as key to lookup registered room
        Returns:
        Room based on stream ID provided

      • joinRoom

        public void joinRoom(Room room)
              throws RoomException
        Logical join of the room which registers the listeners and the Room object to the service.

        This call will also update room details within the Room object.

        Parameters:
        room - Room to register
        Throws:
        RoomException - Caused by room details that prevent logical monitoring of the room object

      • onMessage

        public void onMessage(SymMessage symMessage)
        Callback from registered room listener on the MessageService. All messages will be associated with Rooms. If a message underlying stream is not associated with a registered room, then a new room object is created and events are published to registered RoomServiceListener

        Messages associated with registered rooms are published to room object listeners.

        Specified by:
        onMessage in interface RoomServiceEventListener
        Specified by:
        onMessage in interface RoomServiceListener
        Parameters:
        symMessage - Room messages detected and published
